    "Question": {
      "content": "Which of the following is/are correct about Kirchhoff's rule? <ol type='I' start='1'><li>Kirchhoff's rule is based on the law of conservation of charge.</li><li>Kirchhoff's rule is based on the law of conservation of charge.</li><li>Kirchhoff's second rule states that the sum of average drops in pd across all resistances in a close circuit (closed loop) is equal to the sum of the e</li> </ol>",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "I and III",
        "I, II and IV",
        "II and IV",
        "I and II"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "I and III"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Kirchhoff's first rule (junction rule) is based on conservation of charge, and the second rule (loop rule) is based on conservation of energy, stating the sum of voltage drops equals the sum of emfs. Momentum conservation (II) is not applicable."
